Here's an example of how to do this...

x = read_product_catalog() |>
  filter( product_id == "GLOBAL_MULTIYEAR_PHY_001_030", !grepl("myint", dataset_id))|>  # this varies
  flatten_product() |> 
  mutate(depth = "sur", fetch = "no", mindepth = 0, maxdepth = 1) |>
  readr::write_csv( file.path("inst/lut", "GLOBAL_MULTIYEAR_PHY_001_030.csv"))

Then manually update the values of depth ("sur", "mld", "bot"), fetch ("yes", "no"),
 mindepth (0 or other) maxdepth (1 or other).

GLOBAL_ANALYSISFORECAST_PHY_001_024 - the forecast

As of 2025-03 GLOBAL_ANALYSISFORECAST_PHY_001_024.csv supercedes global-analysis-forecast-phy-001-024.csv. 

GLOBAL_ANALYSISFORECAST_PHY_001_024.csv list all of the P1D (and perhaps P1M) period dataset in 
GLOBAL_ANALYSISFORECAST_PHY_001_024 product group.
